      "stepName": "The Big Idea",
      "explanation": "So, that's the core idea! Gravity isn't a mysterious 'force' pulling things. It's just the effect of massive objects bending the 'playground' of the universe, and other things, even light, following those curves as they travel.",
      "drawingPlan": [],
      "annotations": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Heavy things BEND spacetime.",
          "point": {
            "x": 0,
            "y": -50
          },
          "fontSize": 28,
          "color": "#facc15",
          "id": "summary1"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Other things FOLLOW the bends.",
          "point": {
            "x": 0,
            "y": 0
          },
          "fontSize": 28,
          "color": "#06b6d4",
          "id": "summary2"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "That's General Relativity!",
          "point": {
